Definition: an informant who exposes wrongdoing within an organization in the hope of stopping it
Example: the law gives little protection to whistleblowers who feel the public has a right to know what is going on; the whistleblower was fired for exposing the conditions in mental hospitals
Synonyms: whistle-blower, whistleblower, informant, an, who, exposes, wrongdoing, within, organization, in, the, hope, of, stopping, it, law, gives, little, protection, to, whistleblowers, feel, public, has, a, right, know, what, is, going, on, was, fired, for, exposing, conditions, mental, hospitals
Category: noun.person
